description:
This rule aims to reduce DOM access assigning its object to variable when access multiple time. It saves CPU cycles.
<h2>Noncompliant Code Example</h2>
<pre>
document.getElementById('block1').innerHTML = "Hello World";
document.getElementById('block1').style.width = "50px";
</pre>
<h2>Compliant Solution</h2>
<pre>
var block1 = document.getElementById('block1');
block1.innerHTML = "Hello World";
block1.style.width = "50px";
</pre>
